A two-year-old boy was killed yesterday afternoon after he was electrocuted in a yard of a residence in the Extension 17 Precast Settlement in Lenasia, south of Johannesburg, Alberton Record reports. ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene and found provincial services performing CPR on the child, who was found lying in the yard of the residence. They immediately assisted with performing CPR and provided the patient with advanced life support interventions. READ MORE: Little girl electrocuted while urinating on live wire Unfortunately, after 30 minutes of CPR, no vital signs returned, and he was pronounced dead on the scene. It is believed the child had been playing with some exposed wires when he was electrocuted. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations. &#8211; Caxton News Service